Description: Part of a jar-seal: of brown clay with traces of an impressed inscription, consisting of part of a serekh and a few other signs.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Abydos, middle fort chamber B
Curator's comments: Bibliography: Currelly, Weigall and Ayrton, 'Abydos' III (London, 1902-4), pl. IX, 9; P. Kaplony, 'Die Inschriften der Ägyptischen Frühzeit III (Wiesbaden, 1964), pl.72, abb.269; see also vols. I, 163 and II, 868, n.1003; 1128.
